The online Keychron Launcher, but when I select UK, I lose access to the combined 2/@ key that Macs use. I''m not sure how much of this is down to the OS, do I just change Windows to using a US keyboard? I lose the Â£ key if I do this though I think.

Happy to investigate, just wondering what is possible and where to look next, QMK configurator?

I also thought about just buying another K12 and physically switching the keyboard but I thought there has to be a better way!

  
edit: One more thing - I have the keyboard on Mac mode on the physical switch (I think this just changes the layer?). I can''t get the function (F5) keys etc to work in this set up - is this something I can also do in Launcher? ', 'Technology & Software', 'Keychron', 1, 1, 0.1, '$80M-$300M', 'online', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'open', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, FALSE, 'active', '2025-12-15 17:50:24.226892+00:00', '2025-12-15 23:30:16.221658+00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2025-12-17 00:35:14.981867', 45, 'Multi-OS keyboard configuration pain for 2+ million cross-platform professionals using KVM setups', '$80M-$300M', 'medium', 'low', 'Tech professionals, developers, designers using both Windows and Mac with KVM switches', 4, '["SaaS keyboard profile manager with cloud sync for multi-OS setups ($5-15/month)", "Premium keyboard configuration service for cross-platform users ($49-99 one-time setup)", "Hardware: Pre-configured dual-OS keyboards with instant switching profiles ($120-180 retail)"]', '["Focus specifically on multi-OS users rather than general keyboard customization", "Visual profile builder eliminating need for technical QMK/VIA knowledge"]', '["Niche market - only affects users with both Windows/Mac and advanced keyboards", "Keychron and others may improve native multi-OS configuration tools", "OS-level limitations may restrict what software solutions can achieve"]', '["Survey 500+ KVM/dual-OS keyboard users to quantify willingness to pay for solution", "Build MVP profile template library for top 10 programmable keyboards (Keychron, QMK, ZSA)", "Partner with KVM switch manufacturers to bundle configuration service"]', 'OS-Agnostic Keyboard Layout Manager for Multi-OS Users', 'Users who frequently switch between Windows and Mac operating systems face keyboard layout inconsistencies, especially with special characters and symbols appearing in different locations. Current keyboard configuration tools don''t provide easy cross-platform layout synchronization, forcing users to remember different key positions or accept compromised setups.', '{"original_title" : "K10 Max - compromised set up for Windows and Mac", "original_body" : "Hey all,\n\nMy (generic consumer) keyboard died and I have got a K10 Max on a black friday deal. Pretty happy with it other than a lack of wrist rest but I will buy one.\n\nI use both Windows and Mac regularly, with a KVM switching between the two, the wireless dongle is in the KVM so the keyboard switches automatically.\n\nI didn''t know what kind of hole I have gotten myself into, I had no idea keyboards were so configurable these days. I''d like to create a compromised mac/windows set up for example having the @ sign in the same location on both OS''s.\n\nThe online Keychron Launcher, but when I select UK, I lose access to the combined 2/@ key that Macs use. I''m not sure how much of this is down to the OS, do I just change Windows to using a US keyboard? I lose the Â£ key if I do this though I think.\n\nHappy to investigate, just wondering what is possible and where to look next, QMK configurator?\n\nI also thought about just buying another K12 and physically switching the keyboard but I thought there has to be a better way!\n\n  \nedit: One more thing - I have the keyboard on Mac mode on the physical switch (I think this just changes the layer?). I can''t get the function (F5) keys etc to work in this set up - is this something I can also do in Launcher? ", "subreddit" : "r/technology_and_software", "upvotes" : 1, "comments" : 1, "platform" : "reddit", "url" : "", "confidence_score" : 0.85}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO opportunities (id, title, description, category, subcategory, severity, validation_count, growth_rate, market_size, geographic_scope, country, region, city, completion_status, solution_description, solved_at, solved_by, feasibility_score, duplicate_of, author_id, is_anonymous, status, created_at, updated_at, source_id, source_url, source_platform, ai_analyzed, ai_analyzed_at, ai_opportunity_score, ai_summary, ai_market_size_estimate, ai_competition_level, ai_urgency_level, ai_target_audience, ai_pain_intensity, ai_business_model_suggestions, ai_competitive_advantages, ai_key_risks, ai_next_steps, ai_generated_title, ai_problem_statement, raw_source_data, latitude, longitude, demographics, search_trends, demographics_fetched_at) VALUES (117, 'Man these cows are very LOUD!', '[I wish there was a way where we could mute only these cows.](https://preview.redd.it/iee9w8zahw6g1.png?width=881&format=png&auto=webp&s=1b316aacbc7961da352c4b555c2e883929143df4)

I am referring to the two dairy cows - Holstein and Hereford.  The Prized Pineywood though equally as loud, does not have to be interacted with very often.  But when farming for milk, the two dairies always have to moo before and after the harvest.  The whole experience ends up being too jarring, having to hear the cows moo in quick succession.

I just wished the devs had lowered their volume for quite a bit from the get go.  But with a game that has been out since 2014, it is going to take a miracle for this to be changed.', 'Technology & Software', 'farmville2', 1, 7, 0.7, '$0-$5M', 'online', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'open', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, FALSE, 'active', '2025-12-15 17:50:24.226892+00:00', '2025-12-15 23:02:38.219900+00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, TRUE, '2025-12-17 00:35:20.617449', 35, 'Niche gaming annoyance in decade-old game with minimal market potential or transferable value', '$0-$5M', 'low', 'low', 'FarmVille 2 players bothered by animal sound effects', 2, '["Browser extension for game audio customization (limited to web version)", "Gaming audio mixer tool for selective sound muting across casual games", "Community mod/patch distribution (legal concerns with game modification)"]', '["Extremely niche problem with virtually no existing solutions", "Low technical barrier - browser extensions can modify game audio"]', '["Microscopic addressable market - FarmVille 2 has declining user base since 2014 peak", "Game developer could update audio settings rendering solution obsolete", "Legal/ToS issues with game modification or third-party tools", "Only 7 upvotes indicates minimal validation even within the niche", "User severity rating of 1/5 shows even reporter sees it as minor annoyance", "No monetization path - users unlikely to pay for this specific fix", "Non-transferable solution to other problems or markets"]', '["Do not pursue - opportunity fails basic viability tests", "If exploring game audio tools broadly, survey gamers across multiple titles for common audio customization needs", "Focus on opportunities with >50 upvotes, severity >3/5, and growing market trends"]', 'Selective Audio Control Mod/Plugin for Farming Games', 'Players of long-running farming simulation games are frustrated by repetitive, loud animal sounds that cannot be individually muted without disabling all game audio. The frequent milk-harvesting interaction forces players to endure jarring cow sound effects in quick succession, diminishing the relaxing gameplay experience.', '{"original_title" : "Man these cows are very LOUD!", "original_body" : "[I wish there was a way where we could mute only these cows.](https://preview.redd.it/iee9w8zahw6g1.png?width=881&format=png&auto=webp&s=1b316aacbc7961da352c4b555c2e883929143df4)\n\nI am referring to the two dairy cows - Holstein and Hereford.  The Prized Pineywood though equally as loud, does not have to be interacted with very often.  But when farming for milk, the two dairies always have to moo before and after the harvest.  The whole experience ends up being too jarring, having to hear the cows moo in quick succession.\n\nI just wished the devs had lowered their volume for quite a bit from the get go.  But with a game that has been out since 2014, it is going to take a miracle for this to be changed.", "subreddit" : "r/technology_and_software", "upvotes" : 7, "comments" : 2, "platform" : "reddit", "url" : "", "confidence_score" : 0.85}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
